post_text:
Due to the COVID-19 landscape and the use of several district campuses and facilities as Bexar County voting sites, we will be making the following changes to the 2020-21 school calendar:

October 12 will be a regular school day
November 3 will be a student holiday/teacher workday

This will allow us to deep clean and disinfect our campuses before our students and staff returning to our buildings. Thank you!

post_text:
A message from the City of San Antonio:

The Centers for Disease Control and Prevention issued an Order to prevent evictions during the COVID-19 pandemic.
The Order says that landlords cannot evict certain tenants affected by COVID-19, or they could face penalties. The Order applies only to those tenants that have not paid rent. Tenants that are evicted for engaging in criminal activity can still be evicted.

It is important for you to know that the moratorium only prevents you from being evicted for non-payment of your rent.

You still owe rent. Your landlord can still charge and collect late fees, penalties, or interest. You can also still be evicted for other violations of your lease that do not involve payment of rent.

For more information on evictions, San Antonians can call 210-207-5910 or visit https://covid19.sanantonio.gov/Assistance/Residents/Housing-Evictions

If you someone is unable to pay rent, you may qualify for the City of San Antonio’s Emergency Housing Assistance Program. You can apply at www.sanantonio.gov/emergencyhousingassistance or by calling 210-207-5910.

post_text:
Pandemic Electronic Benefit Transfer (P-EBT) is a one-time food benefit for families who lost access to free or reduced-price meals due to school closures. Eligible P-EBT families will receive application instructions from schools in late May. The P-EBT application will open the first week of June. P-EBT food benefits are for children who received SNAP food benefits for March 2020 and children who are certified for free or reduced-price school meals during the 2019-20 Texas school year. For more
information, visit: hhs.texas.gov/PEBT

post_text: It's time for a morning greeting and circle time with #bestinclass Early Childhood Special Education teacher, Angelina Campos from Elm Creek Elementary! Since routine is very important in this age group not only for learning but also for social/emotional development, she found a way to present her circle routine with a TV, Apple Airplay and using the same order and songs her students were familiar with. She also provided a playlist of other songs and laminated charts for them to follow in individualized packets she gave to her students at the start of distance learning.

post_text: SWISD Business & Finance Office of Purchasing, Budgeting, and External Programs worked together to sew more than 100 face masks for employees working to distribute food to our students in the community. Our mask warriors include Frances Barcenez, Executive Director of Purchasing and External Programs, Donna Schweers, Director of Budgeting, Julie Bradford, Purchasing Clerk, Dixie Zaiontz, Senior Purchasing Clerk, and Christine Rendon, Child Nutrition Supervisor. #weareSWbyChoice #commitmenttoservice #gopublic

post_text: Introducing a new SWISD-TV segment titled "Sights & Sounds of Southwest ISD." Our first episode captures the moment that SWHS Senior, Skylar Stramoski learns that she has been accepted into the US Naval Academy! Skylar has already been accepted to the Air Force Academy, which makes her the first female in SWISD history to be accepted into two academies. She is a member of the Tennis team, Powerlifting team, JROTC, Top 10% and has recently earned her pilot's license. Congratulations Skylar! #weareSW #gopublic

Congratulations to the SW Legacy Girls Basketball Team ("Legacy Hoop Troop") as the FIRST team to earn a UIL State Playoff berth in any team sport at SW Legacy High School!! Please join us in congratulating our team, Coach McWilliams and his staff along with Coach Tarvin and Mr. Guidry on this historic accomplishment!

The Titans will take on Highlands High School on Tuesday, February 18 in the Alamo Convocation Center at 6 pm. Tickets are $5 for adults and $3 for students. District 27-5A, District 28-5A, THSCA, TGCA, THSADA, and TABC passes will be accepted at the gate.

post_text: Sky Harbour Elementary's Dolphin Drama Alumna Paulina Chavez will be starring in a new Netflix series called "The Expanding Universe of Ashley Garcia." The series follows Ashley Garcia, the "only 15-and-a-half-year-old robotics engineer and rocket scientist" in the world, who moves in with her Uncle Victor from the other side of the country for a chance to work for NASA. The series was created by Mario Lopez and is set to be released on Monday, February 17, 2020. SHE Fine Arts Teacher, Dolphin Drama creator, and Elementary Teacher of the Year Carl Dickerson says "he's a proud teacher!" Go Public #WeAreSWbyCHOICE #gopublic #RootEdSkyHarbour

The results from the survey below will help inform a collaborative strategy between the City and County. "This survey will help us better understand what challenges our residents face to getting access to the internet so that we can work with our partners to develop a plan that will lead to a more connected San Antonio,” said City Manager Erik Walsh. The link to the survey is below please help the City of San Antonio collect this information. The survey takes less than 10 minutes.

post_text: The Southwest ISD Administration and Human Resources Department offered four open internships to students in the 18 Plus SET program. This is the first time the District has partnered with the SET program in an effort to open doors for their students in different career areas. The Southwest Employment & Transition (SET) programs allows students to train with various community partners. Southwest hopes to expand the program to many other departments throughout the District. The four students start the internship in December.
